Top Stories (January 3)

CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR URGES US COURT TO REVERSE FERC POWER MARKET ORDER
California Gov. Gray Davis has joined in support of a utility effort to 
reverse a federal regulatory commission order that relies on market forces to 
fix the state's flawed competitive power market.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/03/eng-djn/eng-djn_162032_178_333755524363

REGULATORS CONSIDER GRANTING RATE INCREASES TO CALIFORNIA UTILITIES
State regulators are expected to release a proposed ruling today that would 
grant a temporary rate increase to the state's two largest electric 
utilities, without giving them as much as they wanted.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/03/krtbn/0000-0442-SJ-UTILITY-RATE

BUSH APPOINTS ABRAHAM SELECTION OF MICHIGANIAN AS ENERGY SECRETARY COMES AS 
BIG SURPRISE ON HIS LAST DAY IN SENATE
U.S. Sen. Spencer Abraham of Michigan, a GOP loyalist and policy wonk, 
emerged Tuesday as George W. Bush's surprise pick for energy secretary, a 
position the president-elect has called a priority to avert an energy crisis.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/bellsupe
r/2001/01/03/DTNS/0000-6654-KEYWORD.Missing

DANOIL ENERGY LTD. COMPLETES ACQUISITION OF BASINVIEW
Danoil Energy Ltd. announced that its wholly-owned subsidiary has taken up 
and paid for, in the aggregate, approximately 6,731,159 common shares and 
1,670,000 preferred shares of Basinview Energy Inc.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/intltele
data/2001/01/03/eng-intlteledata/eng-intlteledata_101928_17_6691293064505

EXTENT OF NORTHWEST POWER CRUNCH HAS EXPERTS GUESSING
The Northwest's Emergency Response Team, intent on assessing the severity of 
the electric power crunch in January, pounded away at the available data 
Friday but failed to nail down an acceptable estimate.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/03/krtbn/0000-0375-PO-POWER

